The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro briefs

 Indian airlines Calcutta-Aizawl flight returned after the aircraft failed to land at the northeastern destination because of bad weather. The flight took off at 1.50pm and landed at Imphal. However, when it approached Aizawl, it could not land and returned around 4.15pm. 

 A small part of Calcutta airports main runway was found damaged on Thursday morning. The pilot of Air Deccans Calcutta-Port Blair flight noticed the small dent on the surface at the threshold of the runway while taking off. He reported the damage to the airport authorities and it was repaired immediately. Officials said it was probably caused by an aircraft taking a sharp turn during take-off.

 Two men on a motorcycle were seriously injured when a school bus hit the two-wheeler in front of Jadavpur police station on Thursday afternoon. According to police, the accident occurred around 1.30pm. The injured, identified as Raju Saha and Pintu Bag, were admitted to a local clinic. Police said the bus was not carrying any students at the time of the accident. The driver was arrested.

 Film director Anindita Sarbadhicari lodged a complaint against a youth, who has reportedly posted lewd comments about her on a popular networking site on Thursday. A probe was launched following the complaint. 




